  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For one, this was observed when the underlying cognitive requirement was to understand why the AI tends to confuse two highly similar classes (Colin et al., 2022; Fel et al., 2023).",
    "Moreover, saliency maps can make people falsely accept incorrect AI predictions (Kim et al., 2022).",
    "In all three studies, saliency maps presumably failed to support dealing with incorrect AI predictions because they looked almost identical for correct and incorrect predictions.",
    "Thus, it seems like the findings can be traced back to image-related factors (see Section 5.3.4).",
    "Finally, one study even reported a benefit for correct AI predictions: saliency maps can help AI developers understand that bugs may exist even when the AI is classifying the images correctly (Balayn et al., 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For one, this was observed when the underlying cognitive requirement was to understand why the AI tends to confuse two highly similar classes (Colin et al., 2022; Fel et al., 2023).",
    "Moreover, saliency maps can make people falsely accept incorrect AI predictions (Kim et al., 2022).",
    "Finally, one study even reported a benefit for correct AI predictions: saliency maps can help AI developers understand that bugs may exist even when the AI is classifying the images correctly (Balayn et al., 2022)."
